4. Why this matters (subtle but important)

Take your example:

“Why do bad people have good things happen to them?”

Even inside the Qur’an, there isn’t a single answer. There are patterns like:
	•	Life as a test
	•	Temporary worldly gain vs eternal outcome
	•	Delay of justice vs immediate consequence
	•	Divine wisdom beyond human perception

Your system will:
	•	collect those patterns
	•	weigh them
	•	compose an answer

But it still has to decide:
	•	which verses matter more
	•	how to connect them
	•	how to phrase the conclusion

That’s interpretive assembly, even if it’s very disciplined.

